FT  05 FEB 93 / Barclays to shed 450 jobs
BARCLAYS BANK is to shed 450 jobs in order to centralise processing of
cheques and credit at its Northampton clearing centre.
The bank said it would cut 1,000 jobs in London with the closure of its
clearing centre there, but would create an additional 550 posts in
Northampton. The move to Northampton will take place over the next four
years.
